description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;It is important to note that the role we are advertising is to join our temporary staff bank and is not a permanent position with KCHFT.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The role will be to support services across the Trust as and when there is a requirement for a temporary role. The period of a temporary role will be determined by each individual service and will vary in hours, length of time and base location.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Want to be part of something worthwhile? Do you want to earn good money whilst helping to provide services to your local NHS Trust?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kent Community Health NHS Foundation Trust is currently looking for Facilities Operatives to join their Staff Bank to support Facilities services. This is an excellent, flexible way to earn money and to work when you want to.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunities exist for shifts within our Facilities services across the whole of Kent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Facilities Operatives are good at multi-tasking, are flexible and are kind and responsive to patients, staff and visitors. The role includes cleaning of clinical and non-clinical areas, occasional portering tasks and food preparation and distribution at some sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please review the attached Person Specification document and describe to us in your supporting statement how you meet the criteria we are looking for.&lt;/p&gt;
